HEADWORD: Wagonage
<hw>Wag"on*age</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Money
paid for carriage or conveyance in wagon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A collection of wagons; wagons,
collectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Wagonage</qex>, provender, and a piece or two of cannon.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wagoner</ent>⟦br⟧
